        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 6:15PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 615 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Lapeer, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Lapeer around 620 PM EDT.
Lum around 625 PM EDT.
Brown City around 640 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Goodland Township,
Burnside, Kings Mill, Attica, and Elba.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
